But why Cuthites rather than Babyloniam, Hamathites‚ Avites‚ &c., is uncertain: for thence, as well as from Cutha, were colonies transplanted into Samaria, 2 Kings xvii. 24: nay, they were called Guthites even at that time when a great part of the Samaritan nation consisted of Jews.
